    ],
    "claim": "The contract uses one shared `availableRouters` set for both executable routers and token spenders, and `routerCall` never verifies that `_gateway` is the actual spender used by `_params.router`, so a caller can create an allowance to any allowlisted gateway while executing a different route.",
    "impact": "A single compromised allowlisted integration can be 'armed' by unrelated user traffic and later drain proxy balances even when users route through a different integration, greatly expanding the blast radius of one bad whitelist entry.",
    "paths": [
      "Allowlist contains router A and gateway/spender B.",
      "Caller invokes `routerCall` with `_params.router = A` and `_gateway = B`.",
      "The route succeeds through A, but B still receives a max allowance and can later drain the proxy."
    ]
  },
